lines.text: THIS AGREEMENT, made and entered into this 29th day of July
in the State of California, by and between State of California, through its duly elected or appointed,
TITLE OF OFFICER ACTING FOR STATE
THE REGENTS OF THE UNIVERSITY OF CALIFORNIA, UNIVERSITY OF CALIFORNIA SAN DIEGO
WITNESSETH: That the Contractor for and in consideration of the covenants, conditions, agreements, and stipulations of the
State hereinafter expressed, does hereby agree to furnish to the State services and materials, as follows:
(Set forth service to be rendered by Contractor, amount to be paid Contractor, time for performance or completion, and attach plans and specifications, if any.)
The attached project titled "Iron and Copper Fortification of Milk", marked
Exhibit A, submitted to Dairy Council of California, is hereby made a part
Said project will be completed not later than March 31, 1977.
The total amount to be paid by the Dairy Council of California to Contractor
under the terms of this agreement shall not exceed $4,999, payable as follows:
$2,599 upon approval of this agreement by the Director of the Department of
Food and Agriculture, $1, 200 on or about November 1, and $1, 200 upon comple-
Any item of inventoriable equipment which is purchased at a cost of $1, 000 or
more with funds paid by the State pursuant to this contract shall be the
property of the State for three years following date of purchase. Immediately
upon assuming custody of such equipment, contractor agrees to execute an
"Equipment Loan Agreement Form" or similar instrument evidenceing its possession
The provisions on the reverse side hereof constitute a part of this agreement.
IN WITNESS WHEREOF, this agreement has been executed by the parties hereto, upon the date first above written.
CONTRACTOR (IF OTHER THAN AN INDIVIDUAL, STATE WHETHER A CORPORATION,

SIGNATURE OF OFFICER SIGNING ON BEHALF OF THE AGENCY
